{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2817"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of office machinery and equipment (except computers and peripheral equipment)"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2817"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :office-machinery/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :electrical-safety :product-quality-integrity]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :office-machinery-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "OfficeMachOpsAdvisor ⊣ Office Machinery Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for office-machinery manufacturing (typewriters,
 calculators, cash registers, photocopiers, duplicating machines,
 postage meters, adding machines -- non-computer office equipment,
 precision assembly/test-bench lines) -- not direct assembly/test-
 bench-equipment control authority and not a safety-certification
 authority (e.g. UL listing / CE marking under applicable electrical-
 safety and machinery directives). Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Twelve concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct assembly/test-bench-equipment control), permanent
 equipment-actuate block, permanent safety-certification-authority
 block (this actor never self-issues a UL/CE-type electrical-safety or
 mechanical-safety compliance mark), independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own
 logged production quantity, double-schedule guard, product-type
 validation, dielectric-withstand-test plausibility validation, and
 defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging
 (electrical-safety/mechanical-safety/UL-CE-compliance concern) ALWAYS
 escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the
 only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
